$$f(x) = 4-20x-3x^{ 2 }$$

Write down the first derivative, \(f^\prime(x)\), and find the value of \(x\) that maximizes \(f(x)\). 
What is the maximum value of \(f(x)\)?
solution:
$$f^\prime(x) = -20-6x$$

\(f(x)\) is maximized at \(x=-3.33333\). The maximum value of \(f(x)\) is 37.3333.
